    "The main difference compared to the classical attention model proposed by Vaswani et al.",
    "9 is the absence of positional encodings and dropout layers.",
    "As graphs can be seen as sets of nodes, we leverage this architecture as a readout function in graph neural networks.",
    "For the sake of brevity, we omit the details of classical attention models 9 and summarise only the adaptation to sets (and thus graphs).",
